18. V3 / advanced direction

This is where it gets interesting.

18.1 Semantic dual rendering

Not just hidden vs visible.

Different users/context produce different semantic layers:
	•	public summary
	•	private detail
	•	critical secret layer

18.2 Context-aware risk scoring

Presence requirement becomes stricter if:
	•	in public place
	•	multiple faces nearby
	•	high ambient movement
	•	external display attached
	•	recording active
	•	late-night high-risk access pattern

18.3 Shared-trust mode

For couples/families/work:
	•	some content visible to owner only
	•	some visible to owner + spouse
	•	some visible to any enrolled family member
	•	some require co-presence

That becomes identity-conditioned UI, not just privacy gating.

⸻

19. Failure handling

The system must fail closed for protected content.

Failure cases
	•	camera unavailable
	•	low light
	•	no face found
	•	model uncertain
	•	app backgrounded
	•	system overloaded
	•	external display active

Response

Protected content becomes:
	•	blurred
	•	removed
	•	replaced with safe placeholder
	•	swapped to decoy
	•	hard-locked if strict mode

