23. README-ready summary block

You can paste this almost directly:

# Privacy Window

Privacy Window is a continuous identity-gated disclosure system for mobile interfaces.

Traditional device security answers: “Who unlocked the phone?”
Privacy Window answers: “Who is perceiving this content right now?”

The system uses on-device face presence, liveness, and optional attention signals to determine whether protected UI should be rendered. Sensitive content remains hidden, blurred, or replaced with decoy content unless the enrolled user’s face is actively present.

## Core properties
- On-device identity gating
- Continuous presence verification
- Field-level or app-level protection
- Fast hide / slow reveal
- Screenshot and app-switcher redaction support
- Decoy-mode fallback
- Fail-closed design

## Example use cases
- Private notes
- Hidden photo albums
- Masked balances and wallet details
- Sensitive messages
- Recovery keys and passwords

## Design principle
Unlock is not enough. Protected meaning should only be visible to the authorized viewer.


